PROMPT 95: What are requirements for high-visibility safety apparel for workers near traffic?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- All workers, including emergency responders, within the right-of-way who are within the TTC zone shall wear high-visibility safety apparel that meets the Performance Class 2 or 3 requirements of the ANSI/ISEA 107–2015 publication, or equivalent revisions, except as provided in Paragraph 4 of this Section.
- High-visibility garments must be labeled as, and in a condition compliant withthe ANSI/ISEA 107-2015 publication, or equivalent revisions.
- During daylight hours with clear visibility, workers must wear a high-visibility ANSI/ISEA 107 Type R Class 2 or 3 garment with background material that are fluorescent yellow green, fluorescent orange-red, or fluorescent red in color; a high visibility hardhat meeting the high-visibility headwear requirements of WAC 296-155-305; and
- The Contractor shall require all personnel including service providers, subcontractorsor material persons that are on foot in the work zone and are exposed to vehicle traffic orconstruction equipment to wear the high-visibility apparel described in this section.
- High-visibility garments shall always be the outermost garments.
- High-visibility garments shall be labeled as, and in a condition compliant withthe ANSI/ISEA 107-2015 (or later version) and shall be used in accordance with manufacturer recommendations.
- Flaggers and all other personnel performing the Work described in Standard Specifications Section 1-10, are required to wear high visibility apparel as specified in Standard Specifications Section 1-07.8.[[SRC_1]][[SRC_2]][[SRC_3]][[SRC_4]]

